RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 36300. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 9 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 9 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEEL THE LOVE was forced inward and into Miss Lauren early then saved ground, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, drew to even terms two deep midway on the far turn and dug in determinedly to inch ahead of RIVER REWARDS RVF in later yards. The latter took a quick lead and angled in at the thirteen sixteenths pole, dueled clear of Aim's Jubilee approaching the quarter but was met midway on the far turn then outfinished in a game stretch duel. MIDNIGHT BRASS broke out and made contact with Breadman's Rosebud and was forced in early, settled in the three path on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for third. MISS LAUREN was bumped off stride while in tight at the rail early on then saved ground, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. BAYS CASTLE dropped back from early contention and rounded the first turn about the three path, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. BREADMAN'S ROSEBUD was bumped leaving the gate and saved ground. AIM'S JUBILEE came in early then stalked two deep, challenged into the backstretch and dueled from that point, but dropped back approaching the quarter pole and weakened off the rail on the far turn. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed a claim of foul against the riders of Feel The Love and Midnight Brass for alleged interference early on, lodged by the rider of Miss Lauren.

ENTRY.NAME: Bays Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: dropped back early,chased 7/16,4p far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Feel the Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in,bumped early,bid 7/16,2d far turn,determined lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRACTICALLY THERE raced well back saving early ground, bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced in the six path of the far turn, angled in past the eighth pole, came between horses for the lead mid-stretch and ran clear inside the sixteenth pole. ROSELEE raced off the rail on the opening turn, started a bid approaching the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn in the four and five paths, drifted leaving the turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. MIZZEN stalked the early pace about the three path, dueled for the nod off the rail approaching the head of the lane, but drifted leaving the turn, was caught mid-stretch and relented later yards. SALAMINA rated close inside, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then outfinished in the stretch duel. AWESOME INCENTIVE raced well off the pace about the three path the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path and ran evenly to late stretch before flattening stride. I B NASTY saved ground on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail then flattened inside the sixteenth pole. CHRISTINE'S COSMO rounded the opening turn in the five path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. BET THE QUEEN raced off the pace in the three and four paths then faded through the backstretch. RIDE ON BEAUTY took the lead and angled to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure nearing the five sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, was met leaving the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Practically There
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back inside,bid 3/8,6p far turn,angled in lane,up 1/16,clear

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FULL AHEAD rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn and held on well under steady stretch handling. SLOE GIN BIZ stalked off the rail, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the far turn but was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. SECRET SANCTUARY rated close toward the inside, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and held on for third. CRYPTIC CODE saved ground into the first turn, picked up the chase from the nine sixteenths pole, improved in the four path of the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. WILLIAM'S CAUSE stalked four wide on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole but flattened at the rail on the far turn. SPARKLING SHIRE was never a factor. BAL ROBINSON rounded the opening turn about the four path then saved ground on the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARITABLE VISIT stalked off the rail, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, took over in the three path midway on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on. TRIPLE JEOPARDY rated the pace inside, was met approaching the half mile pole and gave chase through the backstretch, dug in leaving the turn and recovered second inside the sixteenth pole. LOST IN MANHATTAN saved early ground close to the pace, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. TAPPIN FOR GLORY settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and ran evenly in the lane. TYRY TYRANNOSAURUS settled in the three and four paths early on, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and ran evenly to mid-stretch before flattening stride. DUNLUCE CAISSLE saved ground well off the pace then eased out leaving the second turn, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and finished well to pass rivals. NORTHERN RIDGE stalked the earlier pace off the rail, moved to the lead two deep nearing the half mile pole, was pressured leaving the three eighths and gave up the lead at the rail midway on the turn. MINECRAFTER settled off the pace in the three and four paths, gave chase from the half mile pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and weakened. THE IRON BANK showed little response. LIQUID LOUIE raced inside early, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn widest, ducked out mid-stretch then ducked in later strides and lost his rider nearing the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAND FIBER chased toward the inside, raced close at the rail on the turn, dug in for the lead in late stretch and dueled clear the final yards. BIG HAMBONE chased through the backstretch, raced close three and four wide on the turn and dug in through the lane to take second the final strides. MR TINGLES was hustled to the front inside nearing the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, contested the advantage at the rail on the turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn but was caught in late stretch then nipped from second under the wire. MOSS BOSS chased, rounded the turn in the four and five paths and finished evenly. GOT FLOFFY chased inside, raced near the rail on the turn then flattened later yards. IMPETUOUS pressured the pace most of the backstretch, rounded the turn in the two and three paths then weakened. ALWAYS DRINKING chased outside, rounded the turn in the six and seven paths and showed little in the lane. WIZARD OF ODDS and STAR LUCK were not factors.

SUDDEN FLARE gave chase and raced off the rail on the turn. MIDSUMMER NIGHTS eased to the outside, gave chase and rounded the turn about the seven path. NANNY'S MISSION gave chase inside and weakened at the rail on the turn.
